<br>
BB <p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <br><br></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCE6FF><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub103.ezboard.com/uconfound.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CoNfOuNd</A> </span><br><BR><img src=http://peter.armo.co.uk/img/irish.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60><br> <span class=usertitle>Network Special Agent<br />Debates Assistant<br /><img src='http://www.bbarden.com/img/levels/userlevel-admin.gif' /></span><br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m width=80%><span class=m><font color=#FF0000>Posted: 8/15/02 1:22:39 am</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br><span class=title> Re: Advances in science</span><hr size=1> Hi. I am Peter's clone, he is too busy watching Ally McBeal, but I am sure he will reply later. I think clones are great, this way I can do what I do and be who I am.<br>
<br>
Should clones get equal human rights? And what happens when I fall out with Peter and want to live a seperate live, yet I have his name and look exactly like him? Maybe I am Peter after all and he is the clone.. <p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <br><br></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub103.ezboard.com/ulittlelisa222.showPublicProfile?language=EN>littlelisa222</A> </span><br><br> <span class=usertitle>Dissolving<br /><img src=http://www.bbarden.com/img/levels/userlevel-2-1.gif /></span><br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m width=80%><span class=m><font color=#FF0000>Posted: 8/18/02 6:33:33 am</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br><span class=title> Re: Advances in science</span><hr size=1> I think knowing how to clone things could be potentially useful.. But putting it into use, to me, is another thing. Advancements such as that in science are always a good thing, because they allow us to discover more about life and ourselves, and advancements in cloning could help other aspects of science besides cloning.. However, putting actual cloning into use tampers with nature's balance too much, IMO. <p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <br><br></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCE6FF><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub103.ezboard.com/uoldgreybeard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>oldgreybeard</A> </span><br><br> <span class=usertitle>Pebble<br /><img src=http://www.bbarden.com/img/levels/userlevel-1-1.gif /></span><br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m width=80%><span class=m><font color=#FF0000>Posted: 8/18/02 7:02:23 pm</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br><span class=title> Re: Advances in science</span><hr size=1> I am against the ethics of cloning. We should leave nature to itself and not get involved with animal/human cloning. It gives me the creeps! There is a natural balance to this planet and I suppose the clones will eventually balance or kill part of themselves out. So I suggest we do not tamper with nature, it may be our downfall. <p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <br><br></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub103.ezboard.com/uchanelco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chanelco</A> </span><br><br> <span class=usertitle>Ice Cube<br /><img src=http://www.bbarden.com/img/levels/userlevel-1-3.gif /></span><br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m width=80%><span class=m><font color=#FF0000>Posted: 8/18/02 7:03:13 pm</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br><span class=title> Re: Advances in science</span><hr size=1> <br>
   In a way cloning can be beneficial to humanity to fight such things as cancer, etc......the problem is that there will always be someone to abuse it.....trying to create the perfect race...or what they think is perfect, and that is against nature. <p></p><span class=m><i></i></span><hr size=1>   &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fbbardenfrm57.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/reply.gif border=0 width=20 height=20 alt="reply to this message" align=absmiddle></a>   <br><br></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCE6FF><td colspan=2><table cellpadding=8 cellspacing=0 width=100%><tr><td nowrap width=20% valign=top><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub103.ezboard.com/udashofmooo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dash Of Mooo</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.users.dialstart.net/~dashland/html/Strobe.gif" BORDER=0> </span><br><BR><img src=http://www.users.dialstart.net/~dashland/html/lene1c.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60><br> <span class=usertitle>Shimmering Ocean<br />Debates Editor<br /><img src=http://www.bbarden.com/img/levels/userlevel-5.gif /></span><br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m width=80%><span class=m><font color=#FF0000>Posted: 8/18/02 9:10:20 pm</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br><span class=title> Re: Advances in science</span><hr size=1> I don't have a problem with scientific advancement provided it is 'above ground'. Cloning is simply the next small step in a long line of medical advancement, so why should it be treated any differently? It's mainly a media problem, with their biased reporting, portraying images of hordes of cloned humans without rights - who eventually will take over the world. Yes, that would make a great hollywood movie.<br>
<br>
Humans have messed about with nature for centuries, I don't really understand that if we are going to stop, why we should stop now. It's illogical, and again only fuelled by horror stories.<br>
<br>
There is some concern of course. Some major advancements have led to problems concerning our entire future on earth. Take the invention of Atomic energy for instance, or the green revolution, all positive things that may eventually with some imagination prove to be our downfall on this planet. <br>
<br>
But does that make it wrong to invent/develop them?<br>
<br>
I personally think not. Science may not be the solution to all our problems, but it does help us to live the way we are living. Ethically this may be deemed incorrect, but then it can be apply to science as a whole.<br>
<br>
Dash<br>
